OL,3,CMan framed by corrupt police officer
OL,4,Cfor stealing has name cleared
OL,6,F"He came to England in the Windrush
OL,7,Fgeneration and worked for years for
OL,8,FBritish Rail. The conviction caused
OL,9,Fabsolute misery to my dad and our
OL,10,Ffamily.
OL,12,F"Due to the shame and disgrace of this
OL,13,Fconviction, he found it difficult to
OL,14,Fget employment, so much so that he
OL,15,Ffled the country.
OL,17,F"On his return, he became an alcoholic
OL,18,Fand couldn't hold down a lollipop
OL,19,Fman's job.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/10
